I lOVE ❤️ THE FOOD!!! Normally for lunch I’ll go to Popeyes, Wendy’s or McDonalds. Everyone knows I’m a foodie. Good food brightens my day lol. Well, yesterday afternoon, was my 1st time visiting ELECTRIC CAFE, I got the Curried Chicken, smh!! It’s was absolutely DELICIOUS!!! I went back to work telling my coworkers about my new lunch location. Today, my co worker , my  boss and myself ordered food. I ordered the Curried Chicken and Mac & Cheese. Guys,  I want to CRY, y’all it’s so yummy.😋 Dwayne is so nice, he took my order by phone.  I even told him how delicious it was. Signed - Lifetime Customer lol! Keep up the good work. Come on folks it’s only $10. Goodness, some people act like they’re paying 30-50 a plate. It’s the best in my opinion for the amount you pay. Definitely better than Popeyes and the rest, healthier too.

I walked in needing to use the restroom. I understood when they said I needed to make a purchase in order to use the restroom. I explained it was an emergency and I had no problem buying something when I finish. The older gentleman was very rude asking what did I want so I could use the restroom. I even pulled $20 out of my purse and told him he could hold it and I’ll choose something after. He said “I’m not holding nothing”. “While you keep talking you could have had something by now”. I asked him should I just owe in the floor. He said go ahead. I grabbed my money, apologized for inconveniencing him and ran to the Dunkin donuts down the street. They will never have to worry about getting any money from me. I wasn’t trying to get over in him, I just wanted to pee!!  I gave them a 2 star just in case the food is ok but I will never know.

Be prepared to deal with racism and horrible customer service. If I could give negative stars I would. On April, 15th 2017, at 340 PM I was waiting for a friend in the café. I was told that I could not wait unless I bought something. I said I would buy something when my guest joined me. The manager proceeded to escalate the situation and yelled at me to leave because they do not allow loitering. This all happened within my first 5 minutes in the café. The legal definition of loitering is "to delay an activity with aimless and idle stops". I was not aimlessly waiting, in fact I was doing what most people do in coffee shops, reading. Needless to say I left and will never give them business and encourage others to boycott this restaurant so that they leave and we can get a better tenant.
